{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3506491,"name":"Joe Gavin","username":"rhrobotics","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/e68b1a/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-09T04:26:46.635Z","cooked":"

Hello! Newbie mentor here. We have a clean software build but motors won’t spin when given xbox controller inputs in teleop mode or test mode.

Background:
We have imaged our robot for 2025 and confirmed via the REV hardware client that we know the CAN ID’s and we can control each individually.

We have used WPILib (also 2025) to create a clean example code ( using swervecontrollercommand) and we have lightly edited this to update constants, CAN IDs (ports), add an alternate gyro, and send some data to network tables for viewing on SmartDashboard and AdvantageScope. Everything builds and deploys cleanly.

After starting the FRC Driver we go into test mode and also launch advantage scope. We see that the xbox stick inputs are alive.
However, neither left nor right stick inputs cause any motors to spin (our robot is on blocks at this moment).

Any hints of things to check? Thanks!

Our very basic repo is here: GitHub - rhrobotics31324/swervedrive_command_debugging

Thanks!
